<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - Meritor Transfer Cases MTC-4208, -4210, and -4213 -
        Assembly - Transfer Case Shifting Check
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Transfer Case Shifting Check</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply 60 psi (4.14 bar) or greater of air pressure to the front axle declutch (Figure 61).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the input shaft by hand to verify that the front output turns at the same rate as the
                rear output.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove air pressure.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply 60 psi (4.14 bar) or greater of air pressure to the high-range shaft air port (Figure
                63).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303563" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303563.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 63. Apply Air Pressure</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. AIR CONTROL PORT</callout1>
                <callout1>2. BREATHER</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HIGH RANGE SHIFT PORT</callout1>
                <callout1>4. LOW RANGE SHIFT PORT</callout1>
                <callout1>5. NEUTRAL PORT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the input shaft by hand to verify that the rear output turns at same rate as the
                input.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove air pressure.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply 60 psi (4.14 bar) or greater of air pressure to the low-range shaft cylinder air port
                (Figure 63).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the input shaft by hand to verify that the rear output turns at approximately half the
                rate as the input.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove air pressure.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">For PTO-equipped cases, apply 60 psi (4.14 bar) or greater of air pressure to the neutral
                shift location (Figure 63).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the input shaft by hand to verify that the rear output does not turn at all. Have
                someone hold the output shafts to prevent them from turning while spinning the input.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove air pressure.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the transfer case from the stand.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the transfer case UPRIGHT, fill the transfer case with the required lubricant to the
                fill hole level. Refer to Transfer Case Oil Capacities Table in the LUBRICATION AND MAINTENANCE Section
                for volume.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
